<item>
            <title>[LU-13829] kernel update [RHEL8.2 4.18.0-193.14.3.el8_2]</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13829</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Security Fix(es):&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: lockdown: bypass through ACPI write via efivar_ssdt (CVE-2019-20908)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: lockdown: bypass through ACPI write via acpi_configfs (CVE-2020-15780)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Bug Fix(es):&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: provide infrastructure to support dual-signing of the kernel (foundation to help address CVE-2020-10713) (BZ#1837433)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;Regression&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; RHEL8.2 RC - &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;Boston/DD2.1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;RHEL8.2/kernel-4.18.0-193.el8.ppc64le&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; Host kernel crashes while running storage test bucket on KVM guest (iscsi) (BZ#1852048)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;RHEL8.2 - s390/mm: fix panic in gup_fast on large pud (BZ#1853336)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2020:3218?sc_cid=701600000006NHXAA2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2020:3218?sc_cid=701600000006NHXAA2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
